The bespoke kitchen is super modern and finished to a high standard. All appliances are top of the range Neff and wifi enabled. The kitchen is finished with Corian worktops including a boiling hot water tap, 2 large ovens, a multi oven, a built-in coffee machine, induction hob, wine fridge and much more. First floor

Second floor


As you continue to the top floor there is a snug area which perfectly sits just outside 3 spacious bedrooms with high ceilings and Velux windows and a further house bathroom again finished with travertine marble tiles.

The space is fantastic for older teenagers or if you have guests and family visiting.


Cellar


The cellar is the full footprint of the property with 4 rooms including power and lighting which can be used for storage space, wine cellar or further living spaces such as games room and gym or could be a suitable for further development .


External

This guide price can be shown in the form of a minimum and maximum price range within which an acceptable sale price (reserve) would fall, or as a single price figure within 10% of which the minimum acceptable price (reserve) would fall. A guide price is different to a reserve price (see separate definition). Both the guide price and the reserve price can be subject to change up to and including the day of the auction.

The seller's minimum acceptable price at auction and the figure below which the auctioneer cannot sell. 'Living so close to the harbourside and Wapping Wharf is amazing! I’m obsessed with the bowls from Jigaraki and the cakes at Mokoko bakery. My only complaint is that being so close we can’t justify Deliveroo! Starting the morning with a run around the harbour before the crowds arrive is a pretty special way to start the day.

After the hustle and bustle of the harbourside its wonderful to retreat back to our garden oasis. There is a bay tree, rosemary and mint to add to our cooking too. The garden is south facing so it gets the sun all day, and floods the kitchen extension with light. It may be a one bedroom but the rooms are huge so the space can be utilised in whatever way you need.

We are sad to be saying goodbye to the wonderful life this flat has given us but it’s time to get some more space for the toys!'

Coronation Road is situated in Southville, directly opposite the footbridges which lead over the river into Wapping Wharf, an area which has fast become one of Bristol’s most iconic and desirable settings for living, eating and socialising. The area around Gaol Ferry Steps is now home to several stylish homes, trendy bars and boutique shops within both Cargo One and Cargo Two, which came as two phases of retail and restaurant space, largely occupied for local independent businesses. Southville itself has long been one of the most popular parts of Bristol to live in. North Street is very nearby and is home to a number of popular bars and eateries such as The Tobacco factory, the popular Souk Kitchen, The Spotted Cow as well as highly regarded cafes such as Sweven and The Nordic Cafe. Crossing the river from Southville, you are just minutes from all Bristol City Centre has to offer. For those who work in the city, the commute by foot or bike is short and painless, whilst the journey home after an evening in a city is also straightforward and advantageous on foot rather than negotiating city centre traffic.

Nestled away on the basement level, you will find this lovely spacious one-bedroom garden flat. Upon entrance you are greeted by the hallway, finished with stripped wooden floorboards and where you will find the newly refurbished bathroom straight ahead. The bathroom provides a real warmth with its tone of paint known as 'Sulking Room Pink' and is superbly finished with white metro tiling to contrast. To the right, from the hallway, you will find a fantastic open living space perfect for socialising and spending the majority of your time. From the living room you have direct access to the bedroom which benefits from the bay frontage adding to the already generous space. At the rear of the home, you will find the kitchen finished with lovely wooden worktops which contrasts nicely with the dark grey kitchen cabinets. The kitchen benefits from a Velux window providing ample light and from here you can look out into the garden which is the real selling point. Private, south-facing and a lovely size, it’s the perfect space to socialise and spend those summer evenings with friends and family.
